quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  29,15,"But We saved him and the ark's occupants, and We made it a sign for the worlds"
  29,16,"And [We sent] Abraham, who called on his people, \"Worship God and be always mindful of Him. That is best for you if you should know"
  29,17,You worship mere idols instead of God; they are man-made lies. Those you worship instead of God do not have the ability to provide for you. So seek provision from God and worship Him and be grateful to Him. You will all be returned to Him
  29,18,"If you deny [Our message], there are nations before you who have denied it. The Messenger is only responsible for clear transmission"
  29,19,"Have they not considered how God begins creation and then repeats it? That, for God, is easy"
  29,20,"Say, \"Travel throughout the earth and observe how He brings life into being. Then God will bring the next life into being, for God has power over all things"
  29,21,"He punishes whom He wills and has mercy on whom He wills, and you will all be returned to Him"
  29,22,"You will never be beyond His reach on earth or in the heaven, and you have none other than God to protect you or help you"
  29,23,"Those who deny God's signs and their preordained meeting with Him-they have lost hope of My mercy, and they will have a painful punishment"